<subSubSection id="C36696BB8E5EFFB3FF1AFDCADD74FD78" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC3C5308E5EFFB3FF1AFDCADD74FD78" blockId="5.[163,1070,561,670]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
Comment 
<taxonomicName id="4C7CBEB38E5EFFB3FEF6FDCADB52FDA0" authorityName="BOHEMAN" authorityYear="1848" box="[335,559,561,582]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisignatus">
<emphasis id="B90819228E5EFFB3FEF6FDCADB52FDA0" box="[335,559,561,582]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Philonthus bisignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the Afrotropical region. It had been unknown from the Palaearctic region sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEDB8C18E5EFFB3FD1FFDB5DA28FD82" author="SMETANA A" box="[678,853,590,612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref7869" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloeocharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Stenstrup, Apollo Books: 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
until it was recently recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5EFFB3FE87FD97D8FAFD67" box="[318,391,620,641]" name="Yemen" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Yemen</collectingCountry>
for the first time (ASSING 2012). The above specimens represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry id="F36B85A08E5EFFB3FEC6FD73DB78FD78" box="[383,517,648,670]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and the second record from the Palaearctic region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
